# 🛠️ Supply Chain Automation & Core Time-Tracking Utilities

Welcome to the central automation node of my enterprise portfolio. This directory houses a collection of highly optimized Python frameworks engineered to resolve real-world logistical constraints, track dynamic fulfillment milestones, and model systemic supply chain capacity.

### 🧠 Core Engineering Objectives

- **State Machine Simulation:** Intercepting live clock states to perform shift schedule compression and system stress-testing.
- **Risk Mitigation & Business Logic:** Designing tiered alert thresholds based on active time-horizon constraints.
- **Data Input Parsing & Boundary Controls:** Implementing strict sanitization, value parsing, and regular expression (Regex) boundaries to prevent runtime script failures.

## 📂 Production-Ready Frameworks

### 🔹 1. Enterprise Capacity Planner (`calendar_view.py`)
- **Language:** Python 🐍
- **Concepts Demonstrated:** Advanced string matrix manipulations, Regex text substitution, and boundary tracking (`\b`).
- **Description:** Transforms standard calendar displays into a logistics forecasting tool. It dynamically maps out annual timelines, automatically flags high-risk Q4 Peak Season blackout windows, and highlights fixed carrier shipping holidays.

### 🔹 2. Supply Chain Control Tower Engine (`clock.py`)
- **Language:** Python 🐍
- **Concepts Demonstrated:** Multi-hub UTC offset calculations, asynchronous-mimicking loop intervals, and cross-platform terminal states.
- **Description:** Simulates an enterprise logistics control room. It maps global freight hubs (DFW, LAX, JFK), displays real-time target SLA pull-time windows, and allows engineers to fast-forward shifts to stress-test data ingestion triggers.

### 🔹 3. Operational Milestone Analyzer (`countdown.py`)
- **Language:** Python 🐍
- **Concepts Demonstrated:** Chronological deltas, dynamic exception tracking, and single-line terminal rewrite wrappers (`\r`).
- **Description:** A proactive risk-management engine that captures targeted distribution windows, applies manual processing buffer cushions, and projects real-time compounding financial exposure ($ liability/hour) if an SLA breach occurs.

## 🚀 Deployment & Local Execution

1. Navigate into the core utility folder:
   ```bash
   cd Core-Utilities
   ```
2. Execute the desired operational module via your terminal terminal:
   ```bash
   python clock.py
   python countdown.py
   python calendar_view.py
   ```
